    "Finally, to collect our other pairs we manually examined the timelines of the authorities of our debunking and supporting pairs to select tweets that are neither agreeing nor disagreeing with the rumor, in addition to exploiting fact-checking articles (details in Sect. 4.3).",
    "Figure 3 depicts an overview of our approach to construct the debunking pairs of AuSTR.",
    "We leveraged both the factchecking articles and a semi-automated approach which we propose in this work.",
    "Fact-checkers who attempt to verify rumors usually provide, in their fact-checking articles, some examples of social media posts (e.g., tweets) propagating the specific rumors, along with other posts from trusted authorities that constitute evidence to support their verification decisions.",
    "For AuSTR, we exploit both examples of tweets: stating rumors and showing evidence from authorities as provided by those fact-checkers."
  ],
